On 18. 03. 25 14:57, Giedrius TrainaviÄius wrote:
> Hello,
> 
> I'm writing a UCM2 .conf file, depending on Device Tree options, some
> kcontrols may or may not exist - how do I handle this in the BootSequence,
> so alsactl does not error out if some controls don't exist?
> 
> I know there's a possible If condition to check if a control exists, but
> how do I use that to conditionally append to the BootSequence?

Example (from ucm2/Intel/sof-hda-dsp/sof-hda-dsp.conf):

If.amute {
	Condition {
		Type ControlExists
		Control "name='Auto-Mute Mode'"
	}
	True.BootSequence [
		cset "name='Auto-Mute Mode' off"
	]
}

The arrays are merged, thus any additional 'BootSequence []' will be handed as 
extension.

					Jaroslav

